I liked this when I read it, I liked it even more when I read that diary entry, and it got an upvote from me, no question. There are a couple of minor things that bug me though.

First off, the sentence  I understand why this is here, but the placement of the sentence feels blunt and a little jarring. I'm sure there's a way it could be integrated a little better.

Also, the phrase  doesn't seem very clinical, at least where it is. I feel like the description of the handprints as child-like should be alongside the other physical attributes. I admit, though, I can't think of another way to get across the creep factor of the handprints.

Like I said, I like this, and 42 other upvotes can't be wrong. These are just a couple of things that jumped out at me.







